<item>
            <title>[QPID-6387] ChannelToSessionMap/IdToConsumerMap array optimisation publishes in thread unsafe manner</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/QPID-6387</link>
                <project id="12310520" key="QPID">Qpid</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Two internal classes within the Java Client (ChannelToSessionMap / IdToConsumerMap) use an optimisation which hopes to permit &apos;fast access&apos; first sixteen sessions (or consumers) by making use on an array.    The array is written by one thread and then read by others.  Unfortunately,  the read/writes are not protected using a memory barrier so it is possible a thread may see a stale value, and this could lead to incorrect program behaviour.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is safer (and simpler) to replace the data structure with one backed by a ConcurrentHashMap.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
